Sentencas: Zirconia solid electrolyte provides the functions of mechanical support, electronic insulation and oxygen ions conductivity for electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Effect of phase transformation of zirconia on the fracture behavior of electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Ferritic stainless steel is used as current collector to study the structural stability of the two cells during the cooling process.
Titulo: Effect of phase transformation of zirconia on the fracture behavior of electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The sample using fully-stabilized zirconia is cracked after the cooling process, while the partially-stabilized zirconia sample has no obvious changes.
Titulo: Effect of phase transformation of zirconia on the fracture behavior of electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Thermal expansion coefficient of the two samples is similar, which exhibits that TEC is not the main factor to result in the fracture.
Titulo: Effect of phase transformation of zirconia on the fracture behavior of electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In-situ X-ray diffraction results indicated that the conflict between the compression state in cell due to TEC and the volume expansion of the fully-stabilized zirconia sample due to phase transformation can cause cracking.
Titulo: Effect of phase transformation of zirconia on the fracture behavior of electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Partially stabilized zirconia sample can be transformed from tetragonal to cubic phase during the temperature rising, while can be recovered to its initial state during cooling.
Titulo: Effect of phase transformation of zirconia on the fracture behavior of electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Even much more cubic phase can be transformed to the tetragonal phase induced by pressure stress during cooling, which plays an important role on the anti-cracking performance.
Titulo: Effect of phase transformation of zirconia on the fracture behavior of electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cells
